==Finnish==

===Case suffix===
'''-ksi''' ('''-kse-''' ''with a possessive suffix appended'')

# Used to form the [[translative]] case.

===Variant forms===
*[[-ks#Finnish|-ks]] (''colloquial'')

====Usage====
Appended to the genitive singular stem, which is the (weak) vowel stem. 

There's also a first infinitive that has a translative suffix and a possessive suffix, denoting purpose.